article.headline: Austin Peay 79, Tennessee Tech 77 (OT)
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- A Tennessee Tech turnover with 11 seconds left allowed Austin Peay's Anthony Davis to sink a jump shot from the free-throw line for a 79-77 overtime victory Tuesday night. The teams were close throughout overtime, tying four times. Tennessee Tech (11-7, 6-1 Ohio Valley Conference) tied the Governors at 66 on an Anthony Fisher 3-pointer with 31 seconds left in regulation. William Durden missed a jump shot and Zac Schlader the tip-in for Austin Peay to send it to overtime. The Governors (6-13, 4-3) hit 14 of 18 from the free-throw line in the second half while sending the Golden Eagles to the line just three times. Austin Peay began an 11-2 run with two Davis free throws at 8:47 in the second half. The run was capped at three minutes later by a Maurice Hampton 3-pointer to pull the Governors within 59-58. Schlader led Austin Peay with 23 points, Davis added 20 and Durden 10. The Golden Eagles Milone Clark scored 18 points, Fisher 14 and Derek Stribling 11.
